snippet.textDisplay: I used  to call my mother every day. Not once but twice or three times a day. She lived in Curacao and I live in The Netherlands.  Thank God that I used to call her everyday, because I talked to her in the morning,  and when I called her in the afternoon  she didn't pick up the phone,  because she died from an heart attack. When she passed away,  and after the funeral when I came back home,  I was still calling her number.  It took me years to stop  calling her phone.    It will be 5 years this year that's  she's not here and Sometimes I still feel the need to hear her voice thru  the phone . Stay in touch with your parents,  you never know when will be the last time you will hear from them.
